Friendly House in Deitingen -- tContaineranbau in Nantes / House Extension in Nantes Using Containers -- tEinfamilienhaus in Krailling / House in Krailling -- tWohnsiedlung in Chantepie / Residential Development in Chantepie -- tEinfamilienhaus in Riedikon / House in Riedikon -- tWohnhaus in Zellerndorf / House in Zellerndorf -- tWohnhaus in Chardonne / House in Chardonne -- tAnhang / Appendices -- tBildnachweis / Picture Credits0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDespite a growing trend towards sharing, and an increasing number of single family households combined with a growing need for flexibility, the individual single family home remains an extremely popular choice. In addition to following building guidelines, private single family homes are also expected to fulfil high standards when it comes to energy, and often cost efficiency. Nevertheless, they continue to provide considerable scope for architects and designers. Best of DETAIL: Single-Family Homes brings together a collection of relevant highlights from DETAIL. The publication is made up of theoretical articles and a comprehensive section containing examples of projects which provide unique insights into the various applications of wood, concrete or masonry in a range of passive houses, bungalows, double- and semi-detached houses, and villas with swimming pools, from the simple to the luxurious. What these projects have in common is an ambitious aesthetic quality, which can be summed up as good architecture, providing readers with a great deal of inspiration and constructive solutions for their own practice.  aTrotz „Sharing“-Trends, zunehmender Anzahl von Singlehaushalten und steigendem Bedarf an Flexibilität, ist das individuelle Einfamilienhaus nach wie vor eine sehr beliebte Wohnform. Neben baurechtlichen Vorgaben müssen private Einfamilienhäuser hohe Anforderungen an Energie-, meist auch an Kosteneffizienz erfüllen – und bieten dennoch nach wie vor viel individuellen Gestaltungsspielraum für Architekten und Bauherren. Best of DETAIL: Einfamilienhäuser bündelt die Highlights zu diesem Thema aus DETAIL. Die Publikation beinhaltet neben theoretischen Fachbeiträgen einen ausführlichen Projektbeispielteil, der einzigartige Einblicke bietet in die unterschiedlichsten Realisierungen aus Holz, Beton oder Mauerwerk, als Passivhaus oder Bungalow, Doppel-, Reihenhaus oder Villa mit Swimmingpool, von einfach bis luxuriös. Gemeinsam ist allen die anspruchsvolle ästhetische Qualität, kurz: gute Architektur, die eine Menge Inspirationen und konstruktive Lösungsbeispiele für die eigene Praxis liefert.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aArchitecture, Domesticy21st centuryvDesigns and plans. 0aHousing, Single familyvCatalogs. 7aARCHITECTURE / Professional Practice.2bisacsh1 aSchittich, Christian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2015z9783110438642oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2015z97831107009920 cprintz978395553235240uhttps://doi.org/10.11129/detail.978395553236940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783955532369423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783955532369.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-070099-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DKAb2015